accessibility.text: Can the knowledge acquired from learning many different tasks be leveraged to expedite and improve the learning process for new tasks?
Comes in many flavours - we focus on gradient based meta-learning
Closely related to multi task learning- in multi-task is the task provided explicitly
Meta-learning distinguishes itself by its ability to infer tasks and its explicit focus on rapidly adapting to new task
